  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study will be to assess whether forced air warming decreases the rate of
      surgical site infections following cesarean section.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Given the physiologic and experimental evidence regarding temperature regulation; it remains
      convincing that forced air warming is protective against the development of SSI. We will set
      out to prospectively study the effect of forced air warming on patients undergoing cesarean
      section.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
